It's the so-called alt decision tree, a very funny and helpful graphic to tell you how you write an alternative text.

00:36:06.720 --> 00:36:13.720
I know, of course, you can do it in a quick way, that was described in a presentation ago.

00:36:13.720 --> 00:36:23.720
There a thought called a telephone test, explain during a phone call to other person an image in not more than 10 words.

00:36:23.720 --> 00:36:33.720
maybe 11 words, or in a short sentence. How would you do it? There, you get the idea of that image.

00:36:33.720 --> 00:36:44.720
Very quick and easy rule of thumb how to write correct and useful alternative text for images.

00:36:44.720 --> 00:36:49.720
Wah! That's a big journey.

