So, I will do it fast. Fasten your seatbelt, please.

00:37:05.720 --> 00:37:19.720
Well, keyboard support is really crucial, of course for accessibility, keyboard first. So test your web page with the keyboard and without the mouse.

00:37:19.720 --> 00:37:28.720
If you can access all form elements with the keyboard only, then you have an accessible web page.

00:37:28.720 --> 00:37:38.720
If you can reach every link with the keyboard only, you have an accessible web page.

00:37:38.720 --> 00:37:48.720
What can you do wrong? You do not use HTML properly, for example, here's a `span` with the `onclick` attribute.

