Bypass blocks, that equate to topic. Blocks, I do not mean the Gutenberg blocks.

00:38:27.720 --> 00:38:38.000
I mean blocks as sections of the content, of the web page. Repeated on multiple pages, like navigation

00:38:38.000 --> 00:38:50.720
link block or the main content block, or sidebars, and so on. So, provide links to that blocks.

00:38:50.720 --> 00:39:06.720
These links do not need to be visible, the so-called skip links. If you use, let me show you an example,

00:39:06.720 --> 00:39:28.720
Here you can see a page of my localhost, and I am using now the tab key. Once, and you can see here, the skip link.

00:39:28.720 --> 00:39:44.720
Very helpful for users with visual impairment, or use screen reader, and is read, is speaking out loud for screen reader users, of course.

00:39:44.720 --> 00:39:58.720
I use the class `skip-link` and `screen-reader-text`, and I recommend you to take a look in the file `style.css` of the Twenty-Twenty theme.

00:39:58.720 --> 00:40:06.200
and to re-use these statements in CSS for your themes.

00:40:06.200 --> 00:40:10.200
Soon, we will come to an end, I promise.

00:40:10.200 --> 00:40:26.200
Just links. As we have seen, in the presentations ago, provide useful links, because links can be read out out of context.

00:40:26.200 --> 00:40:35.200
Out of the web page context, for example, in a link list, of a screen reader, or another assistive technology.

00:40:35.200 --> 00:40:42.200
So be sure that a link text is understandable out of context.

00:40:42.200 --> 00:40:51.200
What can you do wrong? Well, using the `read more` links especially on archive pages of a blog.

00:40:51.200 --> 00:41:01.200
Then you hear, read more read more read more read more, and you do not know, OK, what's the topic of that link?

00:41:01.200 --> 00:41:13.200
Or you use different link for the same target, that's OK, but not optimal because the link of consistency and may cause disorientation.

00:41:13.200 --> 00:41:24.280
And now you open your windows in new tabs without notice, for me, I think, that is not forbidden but you can do it better.

00:41:24.280 --> 00:41:38.200
How to. Well, provide a link text, which describes the purpose of a link. And uses the same link text for the same target,

00:41:38.200 --> 00:41:44.200
and of course, use different link text for different targets or different web pages.

00:41:44.200 --> 00:41:54.200
You can extend the link text with the title attribute, but be aware that is not reliable because users can turn off speaking of the title attribute.

00:41:54.200 --> 00:42:03.960
Instead, extend the link text with visually hidden unique text. And here you can see an example of that

00:42:03.960 --> 00:42:22.200
I have found that in the theme Twenty Nineteen is a function `the_content()` and you can pass the link text for that,

00:42:22.200 --> 00:42:37.600
for the read more link and with that construction, you can offer a link that you print out only Continue Reading, but

00:42:37.600 --> 00:42:46.200
in the assistive technology, there is a longer description, a unique link. Again,

00:42:46.200 --> 00:42:56.080
then you see, if you put the title of `the_title()` into the link description, and you, so you can

00:42:56.080 --> 00:43:05.680
provide unique links hearing, but visually consistently.

00:43:07.160 --> 00:43:19.680
And how to open new tabs. It's very easy. just say in the link that it is opens in a new tab, in a new window,

00:43:19.680 --> 00:43:32.200
and you don't like the text, you can hide it visually at least it is speak out loud for screen reader users.

00:43:32.200 --> 00:43:42.680
Of course, use a list, a group of links, and use an element `nav` for navigation. A `nav` element is really useful, and

00:43:42.680 --> 00:43:57.680
education, here, if you know where to look it up. I provide you a link because in WordPress 5.5. there's great support for nav element using aria labels.

00:43:57.680 --> 00:44:06.680
Now I come to, I think, the last one. The last topic of the presentation. The focus order.

00:44:06.680 --> 00:44:22.000
Focus is when you tab through the content and you can reach the links, the form fields, every one,

00:44:23.640 --> 00:44:33.680
Provide a meaningful focus order, and let me provide a meaningful sequence, so you get a meaningful focus order.

00:44:33.680 --> 00:44:43.680
What can you do wrong? Use a `tabindex` attribute, oh, yes, there's a `tabindex` attribute that you can control the order of the focus

00:44:43.680 --> 00:44:53.680
while tabbing, or doing tabbing, but you do not know if what happen if the possible

00:44:53.680 --> 00:45:03.680
with other element without the `tabindex` attribute, and the other there is maybe you use the :hover pseudoclass

00:45:03.680 --> 00:45:10.680
for mouse overs, but do not provide the :focus class, too. So, how do you do it properly?

00:45:10.680 --> 00:45:19.080
Use both the :focus and the :hover class, pseudoclasses, and avoid the `tabindex` attribute.

00:45:19.080 --> 00:45:30.760
That's my preferred use no tabindex, just provide a meaningful sequence in the HTML code,

00:45:30.760 --> 00:45:35.760
then the focus order is meaningful too.

00:45:35.760 --> 00:45:41.760
OK, this is my really last. We can squeeze something in not about fooling, about resizing.

00:45:41.760 --> 00:45:49.760
The window, for example, or resizing the content, with the browser functions.

00:45:49.760 --> 00:45:55.760
Well, how can you do it wrong in HTML.

00:45:55.760 --> 00:46:10.760
You provide the `meta` element, but if you put `name` and I have seen that you do not allow any scaling or resizing.

00:46:12.760 --> 00:46:20.760
How to do it properly. A wise technique tells you don't put it in or if you have to,

00:46:20.760 --> 00:46:27.760
allow scaling and resizing, so you can see here in this example.

00:46:30.760 --> 00:46:41.760
Well, congratulations! Now we have come to an end. We have learned the mindset of an accessible developer.

00:46:41.760 --> 00:46:50.760
Text, structure, and keyboard first. And we have learned how to structure the template

00:46:50.760 --> 00:46:57.760
provide a meaningful sequence without CSS first, provide text alternatives, provide skip links,

00:46:57.760 --> 00:47:02.120
and provide tab-able and resize-able content.

00:47:02.120 --> 00:47:12.760
We have some tools which helps you in the world, some data like Nu HTML Checker, or W3.org.

00:47:12.760 --> 00:47:22.760
An accessibility checker online called WAVE, I love that tool, and a text only converter, Textise.

